JavaScript Files:
[OK] smooth-scroll.js
[OK] scroll-animations.js
[OK] modal.js
[OK] lightbox.js
[OK] advanced-search.js
[OK] team-builder.js
```

## Suspected Cause
The main branch index.html references two CSS files that do not exist in the css/ directory:

1. **css/stats.css** (line 27) - Required for styling the Operational Dashboard section (lines 284-327 in index.html)
2. **css/responsive.css** (line 32) - Required for responsive media queries (mobile/tablet breakpoints)

All 18 other CSS files exist and are properly linked.
All 6 JavaScript files exist and are properly linked.

**Impact:**
- **Browser 404 errors** when loading the page (2 failed CSS requests)
- **Broken stats dashboard** - Operational Dashboard section (.stats__container, .stats__grid, .stats__card elements) has no styling
- **No responsive design** - Site may be unusable on mobile/tablet devices
- **Poor user experience** on non-desktop screens

## Suggested Fix

**Option 1: Create Missing Files** (Recommended)

1. **Create css/stats.css** with styles for:
   ```css
   .stats__container { /* container styles */ }
   .stats__title { /* title styles */ }
   .stats__grid { /* grid layout */ }
   .stats__card { /* base card styles */ }
   .stats__card--missions { /* mission-specific styles */ }
   .stats__card--team { /* team-specific styles */ }
   .stats__card--alerts { /* alerts-specific styles */ }
   .stats__card--response { /* response-specific styles */ }
   .stats__card--success { /* success-specific styles */ }
   .stats__card--resources { /* resources-specific styles */ }
   .stats__icon { /* icon styles */ }
   .stats__number { /* number styles */ }
   .stats__label { /* label styles */ }
   .stats__sparkline { /* sparkline base */ }
   .stats__sparkline--missions { /* mission sparkline */ }
   /* ... additional sparkline variants */
   ```

2. **Create css/responsive.css** with media queries:
   ```css
   @media (max-width: 1024px) {
     /* Desktop small breakpoint */
   }

   @media (max-width: 768px) {
     /* Tablet breakpoint */
     .roster__grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
     .stats__grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
   }

   @media (max-width: 480px) {
     /* Mobile breakpoint */
     .roster__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
     .stats__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
     .header__nav { flex-direction: column; }
   }
   ```

**Option 2: Remove References** (Quick fix, not recommended)
- Remove lines 27 and 32 from index.html
- Note: This will leave stats section completely unstyled and site non-responsive

**Investigation Steps:**
```bash
git log --all --full-history -- css/stats.css css/responsive.css
git log --oneline -10 -- index.html
git diff HEAD~5..HEAD -- index.html
git show HEAD:index.html | grep -n 'stats.css\|responsive.css'
```

Check if these files were:
- Never created (orphaned references from incomplete PRs)
- Deleted accidentally in recent merge
- Part of PRs that merged HTML without CSS implementation
- Renamed to other files (check for stats-related CSS in existing files)

